golang 1.2
sudo apt-get install tofrodos
set BUILD_DIR, BOOT_DIR, MAINLINE_DIR, LINUX_NEXT_DIR, SMATCH_DIR, KT_Bot_DIR in main.go,
and all the DIRS are ended with '/'.
maybe BOOT_DIR is unneccessary, you can put the boot script in workdir
and if you do so, do not forget to modify the code of BootTest() function in checkers.go

if you want to use the web function, set database info in sql.go, such as username, passwd...
create the table like this: (otherbugs is the same as patchbugs)
CREATE TABLE `patchbugs` (
  `hash` varchar(65) NOT NULL,
  `kernel` varchar(30) DEFAULT '',
  `bug_info` varchar(1000) DEFAULT '',
  `type` varchar(30) DEFAULT '',
  `caused_by` varchar(100) DEFAULT '',
  `reported_time` DATETIME DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
  `reported_by` varchar(30) DEFAULT '',
  `status` varchar(30) DEFAULT '',
  `comment` varchar(200) DEFAULT '',
  PRIMARY KEY (`hash`)
);
The website will listen at :9090
request ip:port/index and ip:port/upload to view the pages

you can also change the basic text of the email in mailprocess.go

To start the bot, just run 'go build -o KTestRobot *.go', and then run ./KTestRobot
The code remains untested since last edit
